Q6. What is the role of Kube Proxy?
----------------------------------------------------------------

Answer:

Kube Proxy is a networking component that runs on every worker
node. Its primary job is to configure network rules (IP tables)
on each node so that traffic is correctly routed to the right
pod.

Example: When a developer creates a Service of type NodePort,
Kube Proxy updates the IP tables on that node so that any
request coming in on [Node IP]:[Port] is forwarded to the
correct pod.

  • Default mode: IP tables-based routing.
  • Alternative: IPVS mode (higher performance for large
    clusters).

In short: Kube Proxy ensures the networking and routing rules
are in place so that services can reach their pods correctly.

