Q9. What is the role of Kubelet?
----------------------------------------------------------------

Answer:

Kubelet is an agent that runs on every worker node and is
responsible for managing the pod lifecycle on that node.

How it works:
  • When the Kube Scheduler places a pod on a worker node,
    Kubelet takes over and ensures that pod is running.
  • Kubelet continuously watches the pod's health status.
  • If the pod goes down, Kubelet immediately notifies the
    API Server.
  • The API Server then informs the ReplicaSet Controller,
    which spins up a new pod to maintain the desired replica
    count.

In short: Kubelet is the node-level guardian of pods. It
ensures pods are running as expected and reports their status
back to the control plane.

