Q10. What are your day-to-day activities on Kubernetes?
----------------------------------------------------------------

Answer:

As a DevOps Engineer working with Kubernetes, day-to-day
activities typically include:

  • Cluster Management: Managing and maintaining Kubernetes
    clusters — including master nodes and worker nodes.

  • Application Deployment: Ensuring applications are deployed
    correctly onto the cluster with no downtime or issues.

  • Monitoring: Setting up and reviewing monitoring on the
    cluster (Prometheus, Grafana, etc.) to catch issues early.

  • Troubleshooting: Acting as the subject matter expert for
    Kubernetes issues. When developers face problems with pods,
    services, or traffic routing inside the cluster, we step
    in to debug and resolve them.

  • Maintenance: Routine maintenance on worker nodes —
    upgrading Kubernetes versions, installing mandatory
    packages, and patching security vulnerabilities.

  • Support & Ticketing: Handling tickets (Jira, etc.) raised
    by other teams for Kubernetes-related queries and helping
    them understand or solve cluster-level issues.

This is a straightforward question — answer it confidently.
The interviewer just wants to know you understand the practical
scope of a DevOps engineer's Kubernetes responsibilities.

